## Default url feature
### Use cases
#### set current tab url
When set current tab url given the current tab has no url
- it should not save the current tab url as the default url in the local storage.

When set current tab url given the current tab has an url
- it should save the current tab url as the default url in the local storage.

When set current tab default url given the current tab has an url
- it should replace the current tab url as the default url in the local storage.

When set tab default url if unset by tab id given the tab has no default url
- it should save the tab url as the default url in the local storage.

When set tab default url if unset by tab id given the tab has an url
- it should not save the tab url as the default url in the local storage.

#### get current tab default url
When get current tab default url given the current tab has no default url
- it should return an empty string.

When get current tab default url given the current tab has an url
- it should return the default url.

#### clear current tab default url
When clear current tab default url given the current tab has no default url
- it should not do anything.

When clear current tab default url given the current tab has an url
- it should clear the default url in the local storage.

#### reset current tab to default url
When reset current tab to default url given the current tab has no default url
- it should not do anything.

When reset current tab to default url given the current tab has an url
- it should close the current tab.
- it should open a new tab with the default url.
- it should save the new tab url as the default url in the local storage.

#### close or reset current tab to default url
When close or reset current tab to default url given the current tab has no default url
- it should close the current tab.

When close or reset current tab to default url given the current tab has an url and the default url is the same as the current tab url
- it should close the current tab.

When close or reset current tab to default url given the current tab has an url and the default url is different from the current tab url
- it should close the current tab.
- it should open a new tab with the default url.
- it should save the new tab url as the default url in the local storage.

### Presentation
#### pop up
When the pop up is open given there is a default url
- it should render the default url content.
- it should be able to click on the set current tab url button.
- it should be able to click on the clear current tab url button.
- it should be able to click on the reset current tab to default url button.
- it should be able to click on the copy current tab url to clipboard button.

When the pop up is open given there is no default url
- it should render the default url content.
- it should be able to click on the set current tab url button.
- it should be able to click on the clear current tab url button.
- it should not be able to click on the reset current tab to default url button.
- it should not be able to click on the copy current tab url to clipboard button.

When the user clicks on the set current tab url button and there is no default url
- it should execute the set current tab url use case.
- it should update the url input value with the default url.

When the user clicks on the set current tab url button and there is already a default url
- it should execute the set current tab url use case.
- it should update the url input value with the default url.

When the user clicks on the clear current tab url button and there is no default url
- it should execute the clear current tab url use case.

When the user clicks on the clear current tab url button and there is an url
- it should execute the clear current tab url use case.

When the user clicks on the reset current tab to default url button
- it should execute the reset current tab to default url use case.

When the user clicks on the copy current tab url to clipboard button
- it should copy the current tab url to the clipboard.

#### Context menu
When the user right clicks on the browser
- it should show the context menu with the default url feature items.
- it should be a "Default URL" group in the context menu.
- it should be a "Set current tab url" item in the "Default URL" group.
- it should be a "Clear current tab url" item in the "Default URL" group.
- it should be a "Reset current tab to default url" item in the "Default URL" group.

When the user clicks on the "Set current tab url" item in the context menu
- it should execute the set current tab url use case.

When the user clicks on the "Clear current tab url" item in the context menu
- it should execute the clear current tab url use case.

When the user clicks on the "Reset current tab to default url" item in the context menu
- it should execute the reset current tab to default url use case.

#### Shortcuts
When the user presses the set current tab url shortcut
- it should execute the set current tab url use case.

When the user presses the clear current tab url shortcut
- it should execute the clear current tab url use case.

When the user presses the reset current tab to default url shortcut
- it should execute the reset current tab to default url use case.

When the user presses the close or reset current tab to default url shortcut
- it should execute the close or reset current tab to default url use case.

#### Tab event listeners
When a tab is closed
- it should execute the clear tab default url use case.

When a pinned tab is created
- it should execute the set tab default url if unset by tab id use case.

When a normal tab is pinned
- it should execute the set tab default url if unset by tab id use case.

When a normal tab is moved to a group
- it should execute the set tab default url if unset by tab id use case.